Team Head and Corporate Security Officer (Job ID: 3372)

Responsibilities:

To work as the Team Head of Security Services Team of Facility Management Department of the Bank leading a team of security officers / security supervisors / security guards providing security services for a portfolio of Bank’s properties and branches;
To act as the Corporate Security Officer providing professional security advice to Senior Management in all-round security issues;
To develop and formula security policies, guidelines and strategies for the Bank;
To set up, run and maintain security systems, identify and prevent hazards of the Bank’s premises, take corrective action and investigate incident;
To monitor and manage the Bank’s appointed security contractor and to vet the security system proposed by the contractor;
To develop and provide security training program.

Requirements:

Degree in Facility Management / Security or related discipline;
Sound knowledge of security and property management procedures, practices, regulations and legislations;
Familiar with various type security systems / CCTV systems;
Minimum of 8 years’ progressive experience (post-qualification) in facility management and/or security service;
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Strong leadership and problem solving skills;
Highly independent with ability to interact with multi-cultural teams;
A very good team player with good communication skills and risk awareness;
Good PC skills in MS Office including Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Outlook.

